NAME
    Lingua::JA::WebIDF - WebIDF calculator

SYNOPSIS
      use Lingua::JA::WebIDF;

      my $webidf = Lingua::JA::WebIDF->new
      (
          app       => 'Bing',
          appid     => $appid,
          driver    => 'Storable',
          df_file   => './df_bing.st',
          fetch_df  => 1,
          Furl_HTTP => { timeout => 3 }
      );

      print $webidf->idf("東京"); # low
      print $webidf->idf("スリジャヤワルダナプラコッテ"); # high

DESCRIPTION
    Lingua::JA::WebIDF calculates WebIDF scores.

    WebIDF(Inverse Document Frequency) scores represent the rarity of words
    on the Web. The WebIDF scores of rare words are high. Conversely, the
    WebIDF scores of common words are low.

METHOD
  new( [%config | \%config] )
    Creates a new Lingua::JA::WebIDF instance.

    The following key/value is used if you don't set key/value.

      KEY                 DEFAULT VALUE
      -----------         ---------------
      app                 'Bing'
      appid               undef
      driver              'Storable'
      df_file             './df_bing.st'
      fetch_df            1
      expires_in          365
      documents           250_0000_0000
      default_df          5000
      Furl_HTTP           undef

    app => 'Bing' | 'Yahoo' | 'Yahoo_Premium'
        Uses the specified app when fetches WebDF(Document Frequency)
        scores.

    driver => 'Storable' | 'TokyoCabinet'
        Fetches and saves WebDF scores with the specified driver.

    df_file
        Specifies the saving path of WebDF scores.

    fech_df => 0
        Doesn't fetch WebDF scores. (If 0 is specified.)

        If the WebDF score you want to know is already saved, it is used.
        Otherwise, the value of default_df is used.

    expires_in
        If 365 is specified, The WebDF score is expires in 365 days after
        fetches it.

    Furl_HTTP => HashRef
        Sets the options of Furl::HTTP->new.

        If you want to use proxy server, you have to use this option.

  idf($word)
    Calculates the WebIDF score of $word.

    If the WebDF score of $word is not saved, fetches it by using a Web API
    you specified and saves it.

  df($word)
    Fetches WebDF score of $word.

    If the WebDF score of $word is not saved, fetches it by using the Web
    API you specified and saves it.

